From 85bed4ef670df25c19f9a5493aabc6f53e2f3826 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: danclewis <dan.c.lewis@hpe.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 14:20:52 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add BmcTempSensor daemon for BMC SoC core temperature

The BMC SoC core temperature is exposed via the kernel coretemp driver
as a platform hwmon device (c0000130.coretemp) rather than an I2C device.
HwmonTempSensor cannot handle it because it matches devices by I2C
bus/address which platform devices do not have.

Add a dedicated hpe-temp sensor daemon that:
- Scans /sys/class/hwmon for temp*_input files
- Identifies the BMC SoC coretemp device by its sysfs symlink suffix
- Matches it against a BmcTempSensor Entity Manager configuration
- Publishes the reading to D-Bus as a standard Sensor.Value object
- Supports Warning and Critical thresholds from Entity Manager config

This allows gxp-dbus-sensors to be removed from the build entirely.

Upstream-Status: Pending
